#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.57"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.57:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.57:0.2"
msgid "6. Brāhmaṇavagga"
msgstr "6. Brahmins"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.57:0.3"
msgid "57. Vacchagottasutta"
msgstr "57. Vacchagotta"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.161"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: vacchagotto → vacchaputto (mr)
msgctxt "an3.57:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho vacchagotto paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then the wanderer Vacchagotta went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings "
"with him."

msgctxt "an3.57:1.2"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an3.57:1.3"
msgid "“sutaṃ metaṃ, bho gotama, samaṇo gotamo evamāha:"
msgstr "“I have heard, Master Gotama, that the ascetic Gotama says this:"

msgctxt "an3.57:1.4"
msgid "‘mayhameva dānaṃ dātabbaṃ, nāññesaṃ dānaṃ dātabbaṃ;"
msgstr "‘Gifts should only be given to me, not to others."

msgctxt "an3.57:1.5"
msgid "mayhameva sāvakānaṃ dānaṃ dātabbaṃ, nāññesaṃ sāvakānaṃ dānaṃ dātabbaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Gifts should only be given to my disciples, not to the disciples of others."

msgctxt "an3.57:1.6"
msgid "mayhameva dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ, nāññesaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ;"
msgstr "Only what is given to me is very fruitful, not what is given to others."

msgctxt "an3.57:1.7"
msgid ""
"mayhameva sāvakānaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ, nāññesaṃ sāvakānaṃ dinnaṃ "
"mahapphalan’ti."
msgstr ""
"Only what is given to my disciples is very fruitful, not what is given to "
"the disciples of others.’"

msgctxt "an3.57:1.8"
msgid "Ye te, bho gotama, evamāhaṃsu ‘samaṇo gotamo evamāha:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an3.57:1.9"
msgid "“mayhameva dānaṃ dātabbaṃ, nāññesaṃ dānaṃ dātabbaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an3.57:1.10"
msgid "Mayhameva sāvakānaṃ dānaṃ dātabbaṃ, nāññesaṃ sāvakānaṃ dānaṃ dātabbaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an3.57:1.11"
msgid "Mayhameva dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ, nāññesaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an3.57:1.12"
msgid ""
"Mayhameva sāvakānaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ, nāññesaṃ sāvakānaṃ dinnaṃ "
"mahapphalan”’ti."
msgstr ""

#. VAR: vādānupāto → vādānuvādo (mr)
msgctxt "an3.57:1.13"
msgid ""
"Kacci te bhoto gotamassa vuttavādino na ca bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ abhūtena "
"abbhācikkhanti, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākaronti, na ca koci sahadhammiko "
"vādānupāto gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgacchati?"
msgstr ""
"I trust that those who say this repeat what the Buddha has said, and do not "
"misrepresent him with an untruth? Is their explanation in line with the "
"teaching? Are there any legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism?"

msgctxt "an3.57:1.14"
msgid "Anabbhakkhātukāmā hi mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotaman”ti."
msgstr "For we don’t want to misrepresent Master Gotama.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.57:2.1"
msgid "“Ye te, vaccha, evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "“Vaccha, those who say this"

msgctxt "an3.57:2.2"
msgid "‘samaṇo gotamo evamāha:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an3.57:2.3"
msgid "“mayhameva dānaṃ dātabbaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an3.57:2.4"
msgid "nāññesaṃ sāvakānaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalan”’ti"
msgstr ""

#. VAR: ca pana maṃ → ca pana maṃ te (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.57:2.5"
msgid "na me te vuttavādino. Abbhācikkhanti ca pana maṃ asatā abhūtena."
msgstr ""
"do not repeat what I have said. They misrepresent me with what is false and "
"untrue."

msgctxt "an3.57:2.6"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, vaccha, paraṃ dānaṃ dadantaṃ vāreti so tiṇṇaṃ antarāyakaro hoti, "
"tiṇṇaṃ pāripanthiko."
msgstr ""
"Anyone who prevents another from giving makes an obstacle and a barrier for "
"three people."

msgctxt "an3.57:2.7"
msgid "Katamesaṃ tiṇṇaṃ?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.57:2.8"
msgid ""
"Dāyakassa puññantarāyakaro hoti, paṭiggāhakānaṃ lābhantarāyakaro hoti, "
"pubbeva kho panassa attā khato ca hoti upahato ca."
msgstr ""
"The giver is obstructed from making merit. The receiver is obstructed from "
"getting what is offered. And they’ve already broken and damaged themselves."

msgctxt "an3.57:2.9"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, vaccha, paraṃ dānaṃ dadantaṃ vāreti so imesaṃ tiṇṇaṃ antarāyakaro "
"hoti, tiṇṇaṃ pāripanthiko."
msgstr ""
"Anyone who prevents another from giving makes an obstacle and a barrier for "
"these three people."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.57:3.1"
msgid "Ahaṃ kho pana, vaccha, evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "Vaccha, this is what I say:"

#. VAR: thālidhovanaṃ → thālakadhovanaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an3.57:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘ye hi te candanikāya vā oligalle vā pāṇā, tatrapi yo thālidhovanaṃ vā "
"sarāvadhovanaṃ vā chaḍḍeti:"
msgstr ""
"‘You even make merit by tipping out dish-washing water in a cesspool or a "
"sump with living creatures in it, thinking:"

msgctxt "an3.57:3.3"
msgid ""
"“ye tattha pāṇā te tena yāpentū”’ti, tato nidānampāhaṃ, vaccha, puññassa "
"āgamaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr "“May any creatures here be nourished!”’"

msgctxt "an3.57:3.4"
msgid "Ko pana vādo manussabhūte."
msgstr "How much more then for human beings!"

msgctxt "an3.57:3.5"
msgid ""
"Api cāhaṃ, vaccha, sīlavato dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ vadāmi, no tathā dussīlassa, "
"so ca hoti pañcaṅgavippahīno pañcaṅgasamannāgato."
msgstr ""
"However, I say that a gift to an ethical person is more fruitful than one to "
"an unethical person. They’ve given up five factors, and possess five factors."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.162"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.57:4.1"
msgid "Katamāni pañcaṅgāni pahīnāni honti?"
msgstr "What are the five factors they’ve given up?"

msgctxt "an3.57:4.2"
msgid ""
"Kāmacchando pahīno hoti, byāpādo pahīno hoti, thinamiddhaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, "
"uddhaccakukkuccaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, vicikicchā pahīnā hoti."
msgstr ""
"Sensual desire, ill will, dullness and drowsiness, restlessness and remorse, "
"and doubt."

msgctxt "an3.57:4.3"
msgid "Imāni pañcaṅgāni vippahīnāni honti."
msgstr "These are the five factors they’ve given up."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.57:5.1"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato hoti?"
msgstr "What are the five factors they possess?"

msgctxt "an3.57:5.2"
msgid ""
"Asekkhena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena samādhikkhandhena "
"samannāgato hoti, asekkhena paññākkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena "
"vimuttikkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena vimuttiñāṇadassanakkhandhena "
"samannāgato hoti;"
msgstr ""
"The entire spectrum of an adept’s ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, and "
"knowledge and vision of freedom."

msgctxt "an3.57:5.3"
msgid "imehi pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato hoti."
msgstr "These are the five factors they possess."

msgctxt "an3.57:5.4"
msgid ""
"Iti pañcaṅgavippahīne pañcaṅgasamannāgate dinnaṃ mahapphalanti vadāmīti."
msgstr ""
"I say that a gift to anyone who has given up these five factors and "
"possesses these five factors is very fruitful.”"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an3.57:6.1"
msgid "Iti kaṇhāsu setāsu,"
msgstr "“Cows may be black or white,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:6.2"
msgid "rohiṇīsu harīsu vā;"
msgstr "red or tawny,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:6.3"
msgid "Kammāsāsu sarūpāsu,"
msgstr "mottled or uniform,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:6.4"
msgid "gosu pārevatāsu vā."
msgstr "or pigeon-colored."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an3.57:7.1"
msgid "Yāsu kāsuci etāsu,"
msgstr "but when one is born among them,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:7.2"
msgid "danto jāyati puṅgavo;"
msgstr "the bull that’s tamed,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:7.3"
msgid "Dhorayho balasampanno,"
msgstr "—a behemoth, powerful,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:7.4"
msgid "kalyāṇajavanikkamo;"
msgstr "well-paced in pulling forward—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:7.5"
msgid "Tameva bhāre yuñjanti,"
msgstr "they yoke the load just to him,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:7.6"
msgid "nāssa vaṇṇaṃ parikkhare."
msgstr "regardless of his color."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an3.57:8.1"
msgid "Evamevaṃ manussesu,"
msgstr "So it is for humans,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:8.2"
msgid "yasmiṃ kasmiñci jātiye;"
msgstr "wherever they may be born,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:8.3"
msgid "Khattiye brāhmaṇe vesse,"
msgstr "—among aristocrats, brahmins, merchants,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:8.4"
msgid "sudde caṇḍālapukkuse."
msgstr "workers, or outcasts and scavengers—"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an3.57:9.1"
msgid "Yāsu kāsuci etāsu,"
msgstr "one is born among them,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:9.2"
msgid "danto jāyati subbato;"
msgstr "tamed, true to their vows."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:9.3"
msgid "Dhammaṭṭho sīlasampanno,"
msgstr "Firm in principle, accomplished in ethical conduct,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:9.4"
msgid "saccavādī hirīmano."
msgstr "truthful, conscientious,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an3.57:10.1"
msgid "Pahīnajātimaraṇo,"
msgstr "they’ve given up birth and death."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:10.2"
msgid "brahmacariyassa kevalī;"
msgstr "Complete in the spiritual journey,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:10.3"
msgid "Pannabhāro visaṃyutto,"
msgstr "with burden put down, detached,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:10.4"
msgid "katakicco anāsavo."
msgstr "they’ve completed the task and are free of defilements."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an3.57:11.1"
msgid "Pāragū sabbadhammānaṃ,"
msgstr "Gone beyond all things,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:11.2"
msgid "anupādāya nibbuto;"
msgstr "they’re extinguished by not grasping."

#. <br>
#. VAR: Tasmiṃyeva → tasmiṃ ve (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an3.57:11.3"
msgid "Tasmiṃyeva viraje khette,"
msgstr "In that flawless field,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:11.4"
msgid "vipulā hoti dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "a teacher’s offering is abundant."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an3.57:12.1"
msgid "Bālā ca avijānantā,"
msgstr "Fools who don’t understand,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:12.2"
msgid "dummedhā assutāvino;"
msgstr "—stupid, uneducated—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:12.3"
msgid "Bahiddhā denti dānāni,"
msgstr "give their gifts to those outside,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:12.4"
msgid "na hi sante upāsare."
msgstr "and don’t attend the peaceful ones."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an3.57:13.1"
msgid "Ye ca sante upāsanti,"
msgstr "But those who do attend the peaceful ones,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:13.2"
msgid "sappaññe dhīrasammate;"
msgstr "—wise, esteemed as sages—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:13.3"
msgid "Saddhā ca nesaṃ sugate,"
msgstr "and whose faith in the Holy One"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:13.4"
msgid "mūlajātā patiṭṭhitā."
msgstr "has roots planted deep,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an3.57:14.1"
msgid "Devalokañca te yanti,"
msgstr "they go to the realm of the gods,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:14.2"
msgid "kule vā idha jāyare;"
msgstr "or are born here in a good family."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:14.3"
msgid "Anupubbena nibbānaṃ,"
msgstr "Gradually those astute ones"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.57:14.4"
msgid "adhigacchanti paṇḍitā”ti."
msgstr "reach extinguishment.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.57:14.5"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
